            'text' => 'Are there any existing procedures that you will base your approach on?',
            'content_type_id' => 2,
            'value' => 'In 2014, the Technische Universität Berlin (TU Berlin) established a research data infrastructure. It was developed by the Service Center Research Data and Publications (SZF]); a virtual organization, where the University Library, the IT-Service-Center tubIT and the Research Department of TU Berlin cooperate to support the researchers of TU Berlin in all questions concerning their research data (https://www.szf.tu-berlin.de/). The research data infrastructure complies with the requirements of the funding organizations, e.g. the Deutsche Forschungsgemeinschaft (DFG).

The technical core of the research data infrastructure at TU Berlin is the institutional repository DepositOnce. Another service developed by SZF is TUB-DMP, a web-tool to create data management plans. The IT services of SZF are integrated in the IT infrastructure of TU Berlin that is run by tubIT.

