        Question::create([
            'id' => 171,
            'template_id' => 1,
            'section_id' => 7,
            'keynumber' => 'a)',
            'order' => 6,
            'parent_id' => 170,
            'text' => 'Information about your selected repository',
            'content_type_id' => 2,
            'value' => 'The repository DepositOnce is operated by the Service Center for Research Data and Publications (SZF) of TU Berlin, a virtual organization consisting of the University Library, the IT Service Center tubIT and the Research Department. It is based on the open source repository software DSpace. In DepositOnce research data as well as publications of all kind of disciplines and all kind of formats can be stored.
            
DepositOnce provides a workflow for the description and upload of the data files. There is a record for each data set (research data as well as publications). Each record has a persistent identifier (DOI). Research data may be linked to the corresponding publications and vice versa via their DOIs. Other core functions of DepositOnce are the versioning and an embargo function (i.e. a blocking period for the publication of full texts and research data until a certain date).
            
Operational concept of DepositOnce:
DepositOnce uses the virtual server infrastructure of tubIT. All servers, networks and backup services are maintained by tubIT. The metadata as well as the research data are backed-up at least once a day in form of database dumps and files. A cronjob verifies file checksums once a week and ensures the data integrity.
            
Security concept of DepositOnce:
The DepositOnce servers that store the research data and their metadata are part of the security concept of tubIT. They are located within the DMZ of tubIT and are secured by several firewalls. The security concept strictly restricts any physical access to the data center and any remote access to the servers.
            
Responsibilities for DepositOnce:
- tubIT is responsible for the servers, network and backup services.
- The administrators at the University Library are responsible for the further enhancement and development of the software. They are also responsible for the recovery of the DepositOnce services out of the backup.
            
Terms of use:
- The guidelines for DepositOnce "Leitlinien für DepositOnce" are published on the SZF website.',
            'default' => null,
            'prepend' => null,
            'append' => null,
            'comment' => 'Source: DepositOnce Standard Value',
            'reference' => null,
            'guidance' => 'e.g. provider, operational concept, responsibilities for data storage/backup, terms of use, etc.',
